WEBVTT

00:14.125 --> 00:16.458
-[♪ cheerful instrumental music playing]
-[sawing]

00:16.666 --> 00:20.416
[hums]

00:20.500 --> 00:24.083
Oh, hello there. [chuckles]
You caught me.

00:24.458 --> 00:27.083
Well, you can't have Christmas
without a tree, right?

00:27.625 --> 00:30.833
And you can't have
a tree without a forest,

00:31.083 --> 00:33.708
which is where this story begins.

00:34.916 --> 00:38.625
Have you ever wondered what makes
a Christmas story a Christmas story?

00:39.125 --> 00:42.208
I mean, some folks say if your story
is set during the holidays,

00:42.291 --> 00:44.208
then bingo, there you go. [chuckles]

00:44.291 --> 00:47.166
Christmas spirit just rubs off on it
and that's all it takes.

00:47.625 --> 00:50.500
But me, I think there's something more.

00:51.083 --> 00:53.416
You know how you feel
at this time of year.

00:53.791 --> 00:56.833
A little bit happy, a little bit sad.

00:57.166 --> 00:59.541
Maybe you can't even put it into words.

00:59.916 --> 01:03.500
But if you try,
maybe you can put it into a song.

01:03.625 --> 01:05.791
[♪ sentimental folk music playing,
“Ar Fol Lol Lol Lo”]

01:05.916 --> 01:09.750
Now this song I'm about to sing…
Well, it's mostly nonsense.

01:10.750 --> 01:15.166
But the parts that are not nonsense,
they mean quite a lot.

01:15.833 --> 01:20.916
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro
ar fol lol lol lay ♪

01:21.375 --> 01:26.750
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro
ar fol lol lol lay ♪

01:27.000 --> 01:33.416
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro
ar fol lol lol lay ♪

01:33.541 --> 01:39.500
♪ Fol lee fol o la ro
ar fol lol lol lay ♪

01:39.958 --> 01:44.416
♪ There's lilt in the song I sing
There's laughter and love ♪

01:44.500 --> 01:45.500
[Moon] Whoo-hoo!

01:45.583 --> 01:47.916
♪ There's scent of the pine and blue ♪

01:48.041 --> 01:49.041
[Moon] Yeah!

01:49.125 --> 01:50.750
♪ From heaven above ♪

01:50.875 --> 01:56.250
♪ Of reason there's none
And why should there be for bye ♪

01:56.333 --> 01:57.333
[gasps]

01:57.416 --> 01:59.166
♪ As long as there’s fire in the blood ♪

01:59.250 --> 02:00.250
Shiny!

02:00.333 --> 02:02.416
♪ And a light in the eye ♪

02:02.500 --> 02:03.791
[Moon] Ha! Gotcha!

02:03.875 --> 02:06.833
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro… ♪

02:06.916 --> 02:07.916
[Moon] Whoops!

02:09.458 --> 02:10.916
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro… ♪

02:11.000 --> 02:13.583
[Moon] Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

02:14.958 --> 02:16.333
♪ Ar fol lol lol lo la ro… ♪

02:16.458 --> 02:19.083
-Woo-hoo!
-[Papa Owl] No, no, no!

02:19.166 --> 02:20.833
-[♪ music ends abruptly]
-No, no-- [sighs]

02:21.958 --> 02:23.416
-Moon!
-Moon.

02:24.625 --> 02:26.416
-Not again.
-Not again.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.500
Did you see me?

02:27.625 --> 02:30.125
I've never flown that far
on my own before.

02:30.333 --> 02:32.500
-This was a perfect nest.
-[♪ gentle instrumental music playing]

02:32.583 --> 02:35.000
Now look at it! Look…
look at this! I mean…

02:35.125 --> 02:36.458
You broke it.

02:37.125 --> 02:40.750
Oh. Well, now we can make it even better!

02:41.166 --> 02:45.083
Look what I found. Imagine, a silver nest.

02:45.166 --> 02:48.708
At the top of the tallest tree,
we’d be the talk of the forest.

02:49.041 --> 02:50.750
A silver nest? Uh…

02:50.958 --> 02:53.500
Then everyone will look at us.
Everyone will see.

02:53.625 --> 02:55.458
What's wrong with people looking?

02:55.625 --> 02:58.916
We are owls. [hesitates]
We aren't meant to be seen.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.166
-Now come along and--
-But what if I want to be seen?

03:01.333 --> 03:04.416
Do you also want to be eaten?
All the other creatures in the forest

03:04.500 --> 03:07.208
want nothing more
than to make you their dinner.

03:07.291 --> 03:09.458
-The mice don't.
-If they were bigger, they would.

03:09.625 --> 03:12.333
-The sparrows don't. The--
-[hawk screeches]

03:12.416 --> 03:14.750
-[shushes]
-What is it, Papa?

03:15.208 --> 03:16.875
It was probably a leaf.

03:17.000 --> 03:22.208
A big, scary leaf rustling in the mild
yet petrifying breeze!

03:22.291 --> 03:23.875
Very funny, little Moon.

03:23.958 --> 03:25.916
You think you know
what's out there in the world,

03:26.000 --> 03:28.333
but… [sighs] …you have no idea.

03:28.500 --> 03:31.750
-I have kind of an idea.
-[Papa Owl] Yeah, when you're grown,

03:31.916 --> 03:35.125
you can make your silver nest
in any tree you like,

03:35.208 --> 03:39.708
but it's getting cold now,
and we have no nest at all.

03:40.458 --> 03:42.375
I need you to be a good brother

03:42.458 --> 03:45.250
and stay here with Peaky
while I go look for a new home.

03:45.375 --> 03:47.333
-Can you do that?
-Yes, Papa.

03:47.416 --> 03:50.375
[sighs] Stay very still, very quiet,

03:50.875 --> 03:53.625
and don't go anywhere.

03:54.500 --> 03:55.750
All right, I'll be back.

03:58.458 --> 03:59.458
[sighs]

03:59.708 --> 04:02.875
-I didn't mean to break it.
-But you did.

04:03.458 --> 04:05.291
I bet I could fix it though.

04:05.375 --> 04:07.666
-I just need a few good sticks.
-[♪ playful instrumental music playing]

04:07.750 --> 04:11.208
I could do it before Papa gets back.
It would be a surprise.

04:11.500 --> 04:14.416
But Papa said we have to stay here.

04:14.708 --> 04:17.500
Don't worry, Peaky, I won't go far.
We're in a forest.

04:17.625 --> 04:20.833
-There are sticks and twigs everywhere.
-Wait! Moon!

04:20.916 --> 04:23.916
-I'll be right back!
-[♪ music intensifies]

04:25.333 --> 04:26.625
[Moon] Here's one.

04:27.208 --> 04:28.541
That one might work.

04:29.416 --> 04:30.666
This one's perfect!

04:38.375 --> 04:40.958
-[gasps] Shiny!
-[bells chiming]

04:45.291 --> 04:48.333
[breathes heavily]

04:52.833 --> 04:55.125
-[hawk screeches]
-[moon screams]

04:55.291 --> 04:59.791
-[♪ tense orchestral music playing]
-[Moon screams, breathes heavily]

05:03.291 --> 05:04.791
[Papa Owl] Go, Moon, I've got him!

05:04.958 --> 05:06.416
-Papa!
-[Papa Owl] Go!

05:06.500 --> 05:08.750
[Moon screams, grunts]

05:09.083 --> 05:10.750
-[breathing heavily]
-Are you okay?

05:11.208 --> 05:13.625
-My wing, I think it's broken.
-[hawk screeches]

05:13.750 --> 05:16.416
You're going to be fine,
just stay in the tree.

05:17.208 --> 05:19.958
Stay in the tree. I'll be back.

05:20.708 --> 05:21.833
[Moon] Yes, Papa.

05:23.458 --> 05:26.875
Stay in the tree.
Stay in the tree. Stay in the tree.

05:27.583 --> 05:31.750
Stay in the tree. Stay in the tree.
Stay in the tree. Stay in the tree.

05:33.125 --> 05:36.250
Stay in the tree. Stay in the tree.
Stay in the tree.

05:37.791 --> 05:42.125
-[♪ music fades]
-[chainsaw revving]

05:47.083 --> 05:51.166
-[lumberjack] Timber!
-[screams]

05:52.916 --> 05:55.166
-[truck engine revving]
-[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

05:58.041 --> 06:00.625
-[indistinct chatter]
-[truck engine revving]

06:00.750 --> 06:02.708
[lumberjack] Make way,
make way! We're moving.

06:02.791 --> 06:04.541
Let's go. Come on, come on, come on!

06:09.791 --> 06:13.291
-[car horn blaring]
-[traffic rumbling]

06:13.541 --> 06:17.291
-[groans]
-[♪ music fades]

06:18.666 --> 06:20.291
-[car horns honking]
-Huh?

06:25.250 --> 06:26.291
[groaning]

06:26.375 --> 06:29.666
[♪ sentimental festive music playing,
"Carol of the Bells"]

06:38.500 --> 06:39.500
Oh.

06:40.166 --> 06:43.458
[indistinct chatter]

06:43.791 --> 06:47.083
Steady. I got this, I can do this.

06:47.708 --> 06:50.041
What sort of forest is this?

06:51.583 --> 06:52.625
[screams]

06:53.625 --> 06:55.875
[yelps, screams]

06:57.791 --> 06:59.541
-[water splashes]
-[Moon gargles, groans]

07:00.208 --> 07:01.208
[gasps]

07:03.416 --> 07:04.500
Excuse me!

07:05.500 --> 07:06.750
Oh, Oh, Oh, no.

07:07.041 --> 07:10.875
[screams] Whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:11.333 --> 07:12.333
[groans]

07:15.625 --> 07:17.000
[bystander 1] Miss, are you all right?

07:18.000 --> 07:21.041
-Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.
-[bystander 2] Yeah, you really hit it.

07:21.125 --> 07:23.416
-Is there someone that can take you home?
-Just leave me alone.

07:23.500 --> 07:24.916
-I'm leaving. [grunts]
-[bystander 1] Well,

07:25.000 --> 07:26.583
-can we walk you out?
-[Luna] It's fine.

07:26.958 --> 07:29.166
-Why don't you come with me?
-[screams] Watch out!

07:29.958 --> 07:32.541
[groans, breathes heavily]

07:42.583 --> 07:45.083
[♪ music fades]

07:46.208 --> 07:49.833
Well, hello there.
You're in the wrong place, aren't you?

07:50.416 --> 07:52.375
-Are you lost?
-[police officer clears throat]

07:53.000 --> 07:54.750
Ah! Yes, sir.

07:55.458 --> 07:59.041
Looks like I'm in the wrong place too.
Hey, you take care now.

07:59.125 --> 08:02.041
These streets get a little dicey… and icy.

08:02.208 --> 08:03.208
Hm.

08:05.333 --> 08:06.625
-Food!
-[Moon gasps]

08:06.750 --> 08:09.375
Food, food, food, food, food!
-I'll take that.

08:09.458 --> 08:10.583
-Thank you very much.
-Food, food.

08:11.208 --> 08:13.750
I'm sorry, I wasn't going to eat it all.

08:13.833 --> 08:15.833
-Well, well, well.
-What's going on here?

08:15.916 --> 08:18.791
-Looks like we got a live one.
-Yeah, I'm alive.

08:18.875 --> 08:21.208
-Food!
-No, I'm not food, sir.

08:21.291 --> 08:23.375
What were you eating, kid?
Go back to where you belong.

08:23.458 --> 08:25.125
I'm sorry. I was just hoping
I could get some…

08:25.291 --> 08:27.166
You know, I'm going to stop you
right there.

08:27.250 --> 08:30.291
Uh, look, this is trash, you see?

08:30.375 --> 08:35.333
And trash is pigeon food,
not whatever you are food.

08:35.416 --> 08:37.791
-Yeah, what are you anyway?
-I'm an owl.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
-An owl?
-A little small to be an owl,

08:40.125 --> 08:42.416
-don't you think?
-I… I don't think you're an owl.

08:42.541 --> 08:46.791
Owls are, you know,
notoriously significant beast creatures

08:46.875 --> 08:48.083
of the sky at night.

08:48.666 --> 08:50.875
-No, you're not an owl.
-I promise, I'm an owl.

08:51.083 --> 08:53.708
-Food.
-No, no! I don't want your food.

08:53.833 --> 08:56.625
-I just want to get--
-Well, you can't have it, so stop asking.

08:56.750 --> 08:59.125
-I wasn't asking. I was talking--
-[Pat] For crying out loud.

08:59.250 --> 09:01.416
You want Punt to starve, kid?

09:01.500 --> 09:02.916
-He's starving!
-Food.

09:03.000 --> 09:07.000
What chance has he to eat at all
if he isn't eating trash?

09:07.083 --> 09:08.625
-He's so hungry.
-[Punt] Food, food!

09:08.708 --> 09:11.666
Hey, what happened to your wing anyhow?

09:11.750 --> 09:13.375
Well, it was…

09:14.083 --> 09:16.500
-I got in a fight, and now it's bro--
-Oh, tough guy!

09:16.583 --> 09:19.541
[chuckles] So now you think you can
fight us for it?

09:19.625 --> 09:21.250
-Bad idea, kid.
-[Moon] Wait!

09:21.375 --> 09:23.291
I didn't say that! You said that!

09:23.375 --> 09:25.625
I mean, it's three against one.
You really think you can take us?

09:25.708 --> 09:27.250
-Terrible idea.
-No!

09:27.375 --> 09:31.125
Okay, let's show 'em what we're made of
here at Rockefeller Plaza!

09:31.250 --> 09:34.041
Aw, crap, here we go again.

09:34.125 --> 09:35.583
-[♪ dramatic orchestral music playing]
-[Punt] Food!

09:35.791 --> 09:38.541
-Food, food, food, food, food, food.
-[breathes heavily]

09:38.875 --> 09:40.791
[panting]

09:44.041 --> 09:45.041
[Pelly] Over there.

09:45.166 --> 09:46.875
-[Pat] Go, go, go!
-[Punt] Food!

09:47.416 --> 09:48.416
[grunts]

09:50.833 --> 09:51.875
[grunts]

09:55.416 --> 09:56.708
[Pat] He’s headed down fifth!

09:57.916 --> 09:59.708
[groans]

10:00.458 --> 10:01.625
Hey there, little buddy.

10:01.833 --> 10:03.458
-[Pelly] Gotcha!
-[Moon screams]

10:03.875 --> 10:06.208
[Pelly] Hey, slow down.
We just wanna talk to you.

10:06.333 --> 10:08.416
[Moon screaming]

10:09.500 --> 10:11.250
[screams]

10:13.708 --> 10:14.958
[groans, gasps]

10:15.333 --> 10:17.083
[Pelly] Oh, we got you now!

10:17.291 --> 10:19.333
[pants]

10:21.916 --> 10:23.250
[train horn honking]

10:25.291 --> 10:26.291
[grunts]

10:28.958 --> 10:32.375
No, no, no, no, no! [screams]

10:32.750 --> 10:35.375
[grunts, groans]

10:35.916 --> 10:39.125
-[♪ music fades]
-[pants]

10:39.833 --> 10:42.333
-[Moon sighing]
-[♪ gentle instrumental music playing]

10:43.875 --> 10:46.458
-You again.
-You again.

10:49.625 --> 10:52.041
-What is this thing?
-Hey there.

10:52.166 --> 10:55.458
-What sort of forest do you live in?
-How'd you get so far from home?

10:55.625 --> 10:56.666
Is it near here?

10:57.458 --> 10:58.875
What happened to your wing?

10:59.000 --> 11:00.958
-[gasps]
-Is it broken?

11:01.541 --> 11:04.000
As if the holidays
weren't stressful enough already.

11:05.208 --> 11:06.250
It's okay.

11:07.083 --> 11:09.583
Come on, poor little guy.

11:10.500 --> 11:11.666
There we go.

11:12.666 --> 11:14.208
My name is Luna.

11:14.416 --> 11:16.958
You have the kindest face
I've seen all day.

11:17.541 --> 11:19.791
-My name is Moon.
-Do you have a name?

11:19.916 --> 11:23.250
-Papa calls me "Little Moon."
-What should I call you?

11:23.333 --> 11:28.500
Someday, I guess I'll be Big Moon.
But for now, I'm mostly just little.

11:29.041 --> 11:30.708
You have a lot to say.

11:30.833 --> 11:33.958
Oh. Is your leg supposed to be like that?

11:34.125 --> 11:35.791
[♪ gentle acoustic music playing,
“It’s Christmas Today"]

11:35.958 --> 11:41.041
♪ When the Christmas Spirit
cannot be found… ♪

11:41.875 --> 11:44.333
I've never been on the train alone before.

11:45.250 --> 11:46.708
We're right here,

11:47.041 --> 11:49.666
but my mom and I live
down here somewhere.

11:50.208 --> 11:53.208
I guess we could take
this train to this train.

11:53.583 --> 11:57.125
But if I go back home,
she'll be mad at me.

11:57.208 --> 11:59.333
-Hey! Hey, kid!
-[Luna] My dad lives up here…

11:59.458 --> 12:03.000
-[speaking indistinctly]
-This is not your place. This is my place.

12:03.125 --> 12:04.791
-All of this.
-Yes, sir.

12:04.875 --> 12:08.166
I've peed all over it.

12:08.291 --> 12:10.791
-Okay.
-[Dave] Merry Christmas.

12:10.875 --> 12:12.583
[Luna] And here's Rockefeller Plaza.

12:12.750 --> 12:15.500
-That's where we came from.
-Papa said to wait in the tree.

12:15.625 --> 12:17.208
I just wanted to go skating.

12:17.291 --> 12:20.041
You haven't seen
a tree around here, have you?

12:26.291 --> 12:29.166
I used to think Christmas
was the best time to be in the city.

12:29.291 --> 12:31.125
[Moon] I don't understand
this place at all.

12:31.208 --> 12:33.791
I'd come here with my parents
to look at the windows

12:33.958 --> 12:36.166
-and all the decorations.
-In my forest,

12:36.291 --> 12:38.416
we had humans come
to us every now and again.

12:38.500 --> 12:42.500
-I thought everyone seemed so happy.
-And my papa didn't like them.

12:42.625 --> 12:45.166
But I would always give them my best trick
and they'd smile.

12:45.541 --> 12:47.708
None of them look like they do here.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.500
Who knows? Maybe they're not happy.

12:51.166 --> 12:53.125
Maybe they're all alone, like us,

12:53.291 --> 12:55.416
-just waiting for Christmas to be…
-[gasps]

12:55.708 --> 12:57.000
-[cuckoo clock chiming]
-[Luna] Oh!

12:57.125 --> 12:59.416
-What is it?
-I think it's my papa!

12:59.583 --> 13:02.125
[cuckoo clock chiming]

13:04.625 --> 13:05.833
It's just a clock.

13:07.375 --> 13:08.541
Are you okay?

13:10.125 --> 13:11.333
You aren't, are you?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.958
Well, neither am I.

13:15.583 --> 13:17.250
But I am hungry.

13:17.333 --> 13:19.875
-What about you?
-You're saying food?

13:20.041 --> 13:23.958
-You know. Eating? Food?
-I could eat food.

13:24.083 --> 13:25.083
¿Come?

13:25.166 --> 13:28.291
I like worms, insects,
grubs, or small mice.

13:28.666 --> 13:30.291
Do you have any of those?

13:34.041 --> 13:36.708
This is all five bucks
will get you in New York City.

13:39.166 --> 13:42.708
-Pretty good though, don't you think?
-This is the worst food I've ever eaten.

13:43.458 --> 13:45.208
But you're very kind to hunt it for me.

13:46.041 --> 13:48.333
You remind me of my dog, you know?

13:48.833 --> 13:52.208
You've got the same eyes.
You look like you understand.

13:52.833 --> 13:55.625
You're pointing to your heart?
You love me?

13:56.208 --> 14:00.125
I don't know you well,
but I think… I love you too.

14:04.750 --> 14:07.375
Sorry, it's really starting to hurt.

14:07.458 --> 14:10.000
That might be the coolest thing
I've ever seen.

14:10.791 --> 14:12.833
I can turn my head all the way around.

14:15.583 --> 14:18.666
Not as good as the leg, but something.

14:19.708 --> 14:22.541
[sighs] We're quite a pair, aren't we?

14:22.666 --> 14:24.958
[♪ gentle acoustic music continues]

14:25.125 --> 14:28.541
♪ …on Christmas ♪

14:29.000 --> 14:30.541
-There it is!
-[Luna] What is it?

14:30.625 --> 14:32.625
[Moon] The tree, the tree! Look, look!

14:32.750 --> 14:35.083
-What are you trying to say?
-That's where I need to go!

14:35.208 --> 14:36.916
-[Luna] Wait!
-That's the tree!

14:37.000 --> 14:38.083
-[Luna] Come back.
-That's the tree!

14:38.250 --> 14:40.250
-[Luna] Slow down.
-Papa said to stay in the tree.

14:40.375 --> 14:41.708
-Stop!
-[Moon panting]

14:41.833 --> 14:44.250
-I'm not as fast as you!
-[Moon] It’s getting away!

14:44.333 --> 14:46.166
-[car honks]
-[Luna] Wait, I can't keep up!

14:46.333 --> 14:47.333
[Moon] Oh, no!

14:48.208 --> 14:49.250
[Luna] Stop!

14:49.541 --> 14:51.916
-[Moon] It's gone.
-[Luna panting]

14:52.791 --> 14:54.416
[♪ gentle acoustic music continues]

15:02.291 --> 15:04.000
-I wanna go home.
-I wanna go home.

15:14.291 --> 15:15.833
-[string snaps]
-[♪ music stops]

15:16.041 --> 15:17.041
Huh?

15:19.208 --> 15:20.333
Guess it's broken.

15:21.958 --> 15:25.416
Oh well, that hasn't ever
stopped me before.

15:26.791 --> 15:31.041
♪ In the bleak midwinter ♪

15:31.166 --> 15:35.666
♪ Frosty wind made moan ♪

15:35.916 --> 15:39.958
♪ Earth stood hard as iron ♪

15:40.541 --> 15:44.625
♪ Water like a stone ♪

15:45.083 --> 15:49.208
♪ Snow had fallen, snow on snow… ♪

15:49.291 --> 15:50.750
[Pat] Well, well, well.

15:51.458 --> 15:54.791
-Look who it is.
-We thought we'd lost you.

15:54.875 --> 15:57.000
-Food.
-Go away!

15:57.083 --> 16:00.000
You're just a bunch of loud bullies,
and we don't want your trash!

16:00.083 --> 16:02.333
We're lost and we just want to get home.

16:02.416 --> 16:06.666
-Yeah, for Christmas.
-Yeah, for Christmas. Whatever that is.

16:08.125 --> 16:11.458
-Did I just hear you?
-Did you just hear me?

16:11.791 --> 16:12.833
Ah…

16:13.166 --> 16:17.875
-For the Christmas, huh.
-Home is a good place to be on Christmas.

16:17.958 --> 16:20.250
-Wish we had a home.
-We do have a home.

16:20.333 --> 16:22.916
Oh, yeah, that's right.
We do, the streets.

16:23.083 --> 16:26.333
-Food.
-What do you think, boss? Should we?

16:26.458 --> 16:32.208
I guess we could show you the way back,
you know, if you, uh, really wanted.

16:32.708 --> 16:34.333
-You would?
-Yeah.

16:34.416 --> 16:37.416
-Think of it as a welcome present.
-To the Big Apple!

16:37.833 --> 16:41.083
-Apples have worms in them.
-They do, that's the yummy part.

16:41.708 --> 16:44.708
-Come on.
-But my wing's broken, I can't fly.

16:44.791 --> 16:48.791
Fly? You think we fly?
You're nuts, kid. Come on!

16:48.916 --> 16:50.875
[♪ whimsical instrumental music playing]

16:51.000 --> 16:52.041
Oh, yeah.

16:52.125 --> 16:55.500
-This is more like it.
-I do wish I brought my scarf.

16:55.666 --> 16:58.666
You didn't think we were actually
going to fly all the way there, did you?

16:58.750 --> 17:01.291
[Pelly] We're pigeons,
give us some credit.

17:06.791 --> 17:08.208
Shiny.

17:09.875 --> 17:11.708
[♪ uplifting festive music playing]

17:11.833 --> 17:14.958
-There it is, there it is, there it is!
-Wait, let me help you!

17:15.458 --> 17:18.458
I've got to get to the top
before my papa gets here.

17:19.208 --> 17:22.000
Huh? Okay, what? We're running now?

17:23.791 --> 17:26.291
Just stop. This is completely out of line.

17:26.875 --> 17:27.875
Everyone stop.

17:28.750 --> 17:30.666
Stop running. Stop, stop!

17:30.833 --> 17:31.916
-[Moon] Come on!
-[Dave] This is unacceptable!

17:32.041 --> 17:34.333
-[Moon] This way! There it is, come on!
-[Dave] Woof, woof, woof.

17:34.500 --> 17:36.541
Oh, for Pete's sake.

17:36.875 --> 17:38.500
[staff member] Hey, no animals on the ice!

17:40.583 --> 17:43.333
I can do this. I can do this.

17:44.125 --> 17:47.666
I can do this. I can do this!

17:52.000 --> 17:53.458
I got you!

17:54.166 --> 17:56.000
Fly!

17:56.375 --> 17:58.250
-[Moon panting]
-[gasps]

18:01.166 --> 18:03.750
Hold on tight, little guy. I got you!

18:03.833 --> 18:05.291
-Woo-hoo!
-[♪ music intensifies]

18:05.375 --> 18:07.375
-Yes!
-Yeah!

18:07.500 --> 18:10.375
-Holy mackerel!
-Merry Christmas, kid!

18:10.458 --> 18:12.791
Fly high, you brave little owl!

18:21.125 --> 18:22.125
Huh.

18:22.833 --> 18:26.416
It's a pretty good view
from up here, isn't it?

18:26.875 --> 18:27.875
[Moon] Yeah.

18:28.541 --> 18:32.291
I don't see Papa though.
Do you think he'll ever find me?

18:33.791 --> 18:37.916
Well… maybe. Maybe not.

18:38.625 --> 18:41.958
But hey, look at all
those people out there

18:42.125 --> 18:44.708
with good cheer
in their hearts and whatnot.

18:45.500 --> 18:49.166
Maybe they can help you find him.

18:51.500 --> 18:52.750
Merry Christmas, kid.

18:53.916 --> 18:55.333
"Merry Christmas?"

18:56.458 --> 18:58.833
[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

18:59.666 --> 19:03.625
So, what do you think?
What makes this story a Christmas story?

19:04.416 --> 19:05.958
-Is it the tree?
-[light switch flicks]

19:06.041 --> 19:07.541
-The snow?
-[light switch flicks]

19:07.625 --> 19:09.333
-The light in the darkness?
-[light switch flicks]

19:10.000 --> 19:11.041
Or maybe it's that feeling

19:11.125 --> 19:13.208
where you didn't quite get
what you wanted,

19:13.291 --> 19:17.125
but deep down,
you know even one tiny candle

19:17.208 --> 19:20.500
can make things a little brighter
and a little warmer.

19:21.291 --> 19:23.916
-Maybe it's all those things.
-[♪ gentle acoustic music playing]

19:24.000 --> 19:26.458
-Or maybe it's this.
-Excuse me, sir?

19:26.708 --> 19:29.416
There's a little owl in that tree
who needs to find his family.

19:29.500 --> 19:32.250
♪ That's the spirit of Christmas ♪

19:32.333 --> 19:33.666
And I need to find mine too.

19:33.750 --> 19:35.916
♪ Bringing holiday cheer… ♪

19:36.250 --> 19:38.958
[firefighter] Come on, little fella.
You are very far from home.

19:39.041 --> 19:41.750
I have to stay here.
I have to wait for my papa.

19:41.875 --> 19:43.083
-I'm going to--
-[firefighter] Don't worry.

19:43.166 --> 19:45.000
-We'll get you back to your family.
-[Moon] Oh.

19:45.500 --> 19:47.500
-This is very warm.
-[♪ music intensifies]

